abstract: >-
  An open-source reference implementation of provenance engineering for
  AI agents operating in regulated industries. Provides content-addressed
  request envelopes, a hash-chained append-only audit log, a
  jurisdiction-aware regulatory verifier (rules-as-code with adverse-action
  reason codes), engine adapters for Polymarket and SEC EDGAR, an EU AI
  Act Annex IV technical-documentation exporter, and an MCP server
  exposing the substrate to any Model Context Protocol client. The
  architectural rule: AI never produces the source-of-truth number;
  deterministic engines do; humans approve at material gates; every
  action is replayable byte-for-byte under audit. Companion RFC proposes
  the content-addressed request envelope as an MCP extension.
version: "0.2.0"
date-released: "2026-05-11"
